This local Maven repository allows us to use JARs without needing
to run a full Maven repository. This is likely to be superceded
in the future by our own Maven repository.

To install a new JAR, run the following from the command-line (from
the base of the project):

  $ mvn install:install-file \ 
  		-DlocalRepositoryPath=repo \ 
  		-DcreateChecksum=true \ 
  		-Dpackaging=jar \
  		-Dfile=PATH_TO_JAR \ 
  		-DgroupId=GROUP_ID \
  		-DartifactId=ARTIFACT_ID \ 
  		-Dversion=VERSION
  		
This will create the necessary directories and POM files in repo.
  